<p>Residents had previously been consulted on an â€˜infillâ€™ option as well as full redevelopment. But the <a href="https://www.whatdotheyknow.com/request/clichy_estate_ballot_paper_accom?nocache=incoming-1565802#incoming-1565802">info pack</a> sent to residents with the ballot papers asked only whether they wanted full redevelopment or not. Leaseholders were <a href="https://www.whatdotheyknow.com/request/658746/response/1565802/attach/4/Ballot%20information%20requested%201.pdf">told</a> if they voted against redevelopment then they would be faced with major bills. Residents were told that if they donâ€™t vote for full redevelopment then they will likely be faced with the infill option anyway:</p>

